1.

About 1270.

A GRANT by John de Burgo that Philip Basset, may, during his life, pay for the grantor 2osh. annually ad wardam of Dover Castle, due from the Manor of Beeston, which Philip holds from John de Burgo.

Witnesses: Sirs Paul Peyure‚ Richard Bausan, Roget· de Wanton, Richard de Sannford‚ Stephen Bausan‚ Julian de Haya, and Thomas Batesford‚ clerk.

No date.

Ancient Deeds, P.R.O.‚ B. 3911, and compare A. 5577 and C. 2263 for similar grants connected with the ward of
